0.body:
[u][b]DOMINOES:[/b][/u]

This is a basic ruleset for dominoes of 28 and up to double sixes. You can spawn additional dominoes if you need them and can search online for other ways to play dominoes as there are many variations out there!

[b]GAME OBJECTIVE:[/b]
Up to four people can play dominoes. If Four are playing, each person can play individually or you can group into two teams.

[b]HOW TO PLAY:[/b]
The 28 tiles are shuffled face down. Each player draws seven tiles. The middle of the table is the playing area, so you may need to move the rest of the pieces aside after drawing. Move your pieces into your playing hand so that they remain hidden to everyone but yourself.  Every player can see how many tiles remain in the other players' hands at all times during gameplay. One player begins by playing the first tile. You can choose how to begin, but usually the person with the highest doubles (ie. double sixes), goes first. 

The second player tries to put a domino on the table that matches one side of what's already there. If a player cannot go, the player picks one domino from the pile and skips that turn. The chain of the played dominoes develops randomly, and can look a lot like a snake.
Continue taking turns putting dominoes on the board (or picking one from the pile if you cannot go) until someone wins. In regular dominoes, the best strategy is to get rid of doubles first.

[b]WINNING:[/b]
The winner is the first person to get rid of all of their dominoes. But if no one can go out, then the person with the fewest dominos left is the winner.

Please note that these Notepad are one in many out there, but this is a good starting point for one way to play the game. If youâ€™d like to find other ways to play, you can search online. [b]Have fun![/b]
